metadata.name: Katrina
metadata.description:
Katrina was a major tropical cyclone that made landfall on the Gulf Coast of the United States in August 2005. It was one of the deadliest and most destructive storms in US history, with an estimated 1,833 people losing their lives and billions of dollars in damage. Caused by the storm. Katrina was a Category 5 hurricane when it made landfall in Louisiana and Mississippi, with winds of up to 281 km/h.
